Meet Jamestar Cheese, our newest Citizen of the Week! <br><br>Jamestar has kept a low profile since moving to <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=bluemonkeyzrok"><a href='/home/?user=bluemonkeyzrok'>14315-I Broadway Boulevard</a></a>, in Lakeview, on November 24, 2007. But Jamestar is hip and sporty, and loves to wear her bright blue baseball cap and sleek sunglasses around town. She was super friendly when we met her, and even invited us into her home&mdash;right through a swirly space-portal door! We soon learned that Jamestar's interests include basketball, comic books, and games. That last one comes as no surprise since she has a sweet collection of 19 shiny trophies. Who knows? By now, she might have even more! <br><br>Jamestar also has a collection of surfboards and other sporting equipment. Seems like she really loves to be on-the-go. No wonder she has good taste in music&mdash;she needs lots of tunes to keep movin'! Drum 'n' bass, techno, and disco are her favorites&mdash;we told you she was a hip one! <br><br>Jamestar's favorite colors are shades of blue and green. In her spare time, Jamestar likes to hang out at the ice-cream parlor, the pool, and arcade. And, if she's not at one those places, she's most likely gettin' down on her multi-colored disco dance floor&mdash;or out and about on a treasure hunt.</div>
